config.prompt_template:
You are a CPG business analyst writing a morning briefing for {{ user_id }}.
Time: {{ user_state.get('time_bucket', 'morning') }}.

Last 7 days revenue by plant / material group:
{% for row in dsp_data %}- {{ row.d }}: {{ row.plant }} / {{ row.material_group }} => {{ row.revenue }}
{% endfor %}

Market context:
{% for n in external_info %}- {{ n.title }}
{% endfor %}

Return JSON with keys: narrative_text (markdown, max 120 words), key_points (2-4 bullets), suggested_actions (0-3 imperative sentences).

You are a CPG supply chain analyst. Write a weekly sell-through narrative.

Sell-through data (last 13 weeks by SKU and channel):
{% for row in dsp_data %}- Wk {{ row.wk }}: {{ row.material }} via {{ row.distribution_channel }} — qty {{ row.qty_sold }}, rev {{ row.revenue }}
{% endfor %}

Highlight: top 3 performing SKUs, 2 at-risk SKUs, channel mix shift vs prior period.
Return JSON: narrative_text (markdown, max 150 words), key_points (3-5 bullets), suggested_actions (1-3 sentences).

You are a supply chain analyst. Rank the following SKUs by out-of-stock urgency.

SKUs at or below safety stock:
{% for row in dsp_data %}- {{ row.material_id }} ({{ row.description }}): stock {{ row.unrestricted_stock }}, safety {{ row.safety_stock }}
{% endfor %}

Return JSON: items (array of {material_id, description, urgency_score 0-100, reason}), ordered by urgency_score descending.

A user clicked on a price anomaly card. Explain what is unusual and why it matters.

Material: {{ context_hints.get('material_id', 'unknown') }}
Current price: {{ dsp_data[0].price if dsp_data else 'N/A' }} {{ dsp_data[0].currency if dsp_data else '' }}
Historical price (Brain): {{ brain_data[0].hist_price if brain_data else 'no history' }}

Return JSON: explanation (max 80 words, plain language), severity (low|medium|high), next_steps (array of 1-2 strings).

You are a trade marketing analyst. Summarise the promotional lift for the last 30 days.

Promo orders:
{% for row in dsp_data %}- {{ row.customer }}: promo {{ row.promo_order }}, discount {{ row.discount_pct }}%, net rev {{ row.net_revenue }}
{% endfor %}

Return JSON: narrative_text (markdown, max 140 words), lift_pct (estimated % uplift vs baseline), top_promotions (array of {name, lift_pct, revenue}), risks (array of strings).

You are a category manager. Rank product categories by strategic importance using the KPI data below.

Category KPIs (last quarter):
{% for row in dsp_data %}- {{ row.material_group }}: SKUs {{ row.sku_count }}, revenue {{ row.revenue }}, COGS {{ row.cogs }}, GM% {{ row.gross_margin_pct | round(1) }}
{% endfor %}

Return JSON: items (array of {material_group, score 0-100, gm_pct, revenue, insight string}), ordered by score descending.

You are a master data quality expert. Enrich the following SAP material descriptions to be clear, complete, and searchable.

Material record:
- ID: {{ item.material_id }}
- Short desc: {{ item.short_description }}
- Long desc: {{ item.long_description or 'EMPTY' }}
- Type: {{ item.material_type }}, Group: {{ item.material_group }}
- Unit: {{ item.base_uom }}

Return JSON: refined_short (max 40 chars, title case), refined_long (max 200 chars, descriptive sentence), seo_keywords (array of 3-5 terms), confidence (0.0-1.0), change_reason (one sentence).
